summary: DT*: THE CONTACT STATED THE VEHICLE WAS INVOLVED IN A COLLISION AND THE AIRBAGS DID NOT DEPLOY.  THE CONTACT WAS STOPPED IN THE CENTER LANE, WHEN ANOTHER VEHICLE ATTEMPTED TO GET INTO THE SAME LANE.  THE CONTACT'S VEHICLE WAS HIT ON THE FRONT PASSENGER SIDE FENDER CAUSING THE VEHICLE TO FLIP COMPLETELY OVER AND LANDED RIGHT SIDE UP.  THE CONTACT SUSTAINED HEAD AND ARM INJURIES AND A POLICE REPORT WAS TAKEN.  ALL OCCUPANTS WERE WEARING THEIR SEATBELTS.  THE AIRBAG WARNING LIGHT WAS NOT ILLUMINATED PRIOR TO THE CRASH.  THERE WERE PICTURES AVAILABLE AND THE VEHICLE WAS DEEMED TOTALED.
